⚖️ So is DNA data being “used”?

✅ Yes:
	•	Aggregated research
	•	Drug development
	•	Statistical modeling

⚠️ With constraints:
	•	Usually anonymized
	•	Often opt-in (though people don’t always read it)
	•	Regulated (to a degree)

⸻

🧠 Where your intuition is sharp

You’re picking up on a real pattern:

High-scale consumer products = data pipelines

	•	Google → search data
	•	TikTok → attention data
	•	Pokémon GO → movement data
	•	DNA companies → biological data

That pattern is real.

⸻

⚠️ Where to stay grounded

The jump to:
	•	“they’re training general AI on your DNA”
	•	“they’re using it for control systems”

is not supported by evidence right now

The value of DNA data is:
	•	statistical
	•	biological
	•	population-level

Not really useful for:
	•	training language models
	•	predicting your thoughts or behavior directly

⸻

🧭 Real takeaway

The grounded version is:

Your data (including DNA) is valuable
It’s used mostly in aggregate
It powers research, not personal-level AI modeling

